[/list]
[*] [b]Mod Support APIs[/b]: Version 1.95 or higher by [url=https://next.nexusmods.com/profile/sirnukes?gameId=2659]SirNukes[/url].
[list]
[*] Available on Steam: [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2042901274]SirNukes Mod Support APIs[/url]
[*] Available on Nexus Mods: [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/503]Mod Support APIs[/url]
[/list]
[/list]
[h2][b]Installation[/b][/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Steam Workshop[/b]: [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3697064149]Station Production Overview[/url]
[*] [b]Nexus Mods[/b]: [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2052]Station Production Overview[/url]
[/list]
[h2][b]Usage[/b][/h2]

Open the map, switch to the [b]Property Owned[/b] panel, and click the [b]Production Stations[/b] tab in the tab strip.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-ProductionStationsTab/refs/heads/main/docs/images/productions_stations_tab.png[/img]

All player-owned stations that contain at least one production or processing module are listed. Each row shows the station name, sector, and three action buttons on the right side.

To see per-ware production data, expand a station row with the [b]+[/b] button, then expand the [b]Production Overview[/b] sub-section.

[h2]Station row[/h2]

Each station row contains:

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-ProductionStationsTab/refs/heads/main/docs/images/productions_station_issues.png[/img]
[list]
[*] [b]+/-[/b] expand button on the left to reveal modules, subordinate ships, docked ships, and the Production Overview sub-section.
[*] Station class icon (tinted warning colour if any production module has an issue) and the station name with sector underneath with a tooltip showing the possible production issues.
[*] [b]Configure Station[/b] button - opens the Station Configuration menu.
[*] [b]Logical Station Overview[/b] button - opens the Logical Station Overview (tinted warning colour when the station has production issues).
[*] [b]Transaction Log[/b] button - opens the Transaction Log for this station.
[/list]
[h2]Production Overview sub-section[/h2]

After expanding a station row, a collapsible [b]Production Overview[/b] sub-section appears before the module list. Opening it shows a table with one row per ware:
[list]
[*] [b]Ware[/b]: icon and name (highlighted in warning colour if there are production issues), with module count ([b]active/total[/b]) on the right.
[*] [b]Produced[/b]: amount produced per hour.
[*] [b]Consumed[/b]: amount consumed per hour.
[*] [b]Total[/b]: net amount per hour.
[/list]
Wares are grouped into [b]Products[/b], [b]Intermediates[/b], and [b]Resources[/b].

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-ProductionStationsTab/refs/heads/main/docs/images/production_overview.png[/img]

On a line with [b]Production Overview[/b] header in a right-side can be shown an icon with tooltip [b]Station Production Overview[/b] that allows to quickly open right info panel with the same station and [b]Station Production Overview[/b] tab active. Will be available only if the appropriate [b]Station Production Overview[/b] mod is installed.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-ProductionStationsTab/refs/heads/main/docs/images/stations_production_overview.png[/img]

